In a #medium pot{}, combine @Basmati Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Core, deseed, and dice @Bell Pepper{1} into 1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and finely dice @Yellow Onion{1}. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Thinly slice @Chili Pepper{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and onion; season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Stir in garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wash out pan.

> TIP: If needed, add a splash of water to help pepper and onion soften.

While veggies cook, pat @Diced Chicken Thighs{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Add chicken, @Yogurt{2%tablespoon}, half the @Garam Masala{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings), salt, and pepper to a #medium bowl{} and toss until evenly coated.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned all over, ~{2-4%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step). Reduce heat to medium.

To the same pan, stir in @Curry Sauce Base{5%ounce}, @Paprika{1%teaspoon}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, 1/2 cup water (1 cup for 4 servings), @Butter{1%tablespoon}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to low. Cook until sauce is thickened and chicken is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Add veggies and @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon}; stir to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Divide between shallow #bowls{} or #plates{}. Top with chicken and sauce. Sprinkle with cilantro and sliced chili if desired. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.